      "content": "it just feels like you're saying i should just stay here and suffer because it's \"valid\" to suffer. but at what point does \"validating\" someone just become watching them burn? if someone was caught in a house fire, you wouldn't tell them it's valid to feel the heat, you'd help them get out. for me, \"getting out\" feels like it might mean finally being able to rest. it feels like the most compassionate thing would be to let someone go if they can't find relief.",
